keeper’) was the usual term. In North America, the surname <i>Miller</i> has absorbed many cognate surnames from other languages, for example German <b>Müller</b> (see   Mueller  ), Dutch   Mulder   and   Molenaar  , French   Meunier  , Italian   Molinaro  , Spanish   Molinero  , Hungarian <b>Molnár</b> (see   Molnar  ), Slovenian, Croatian, and Serbian   Mlinar  , Polish <b>Młynarz</b> or <b>Młynarczyk</b> (see   Mlynarczyk  ). <i>Miller</i> (including in the senses below) is the seventh most frequent surname in the US.","South German, Swiss German, and Jewish (Ashkenazic): variant of <b>Müller</b> ‘miller’ (see   Mueller  ) and, in North America, also an altered form of this. This form of the surname is also found in other European countries, notably in Poland, Denmark, France (mainly Alsace and Lorraine), and Czechia; compare 3 below.","Americanized form of Polish, Czech, Croatian, Serbian, and Slovenian   Miler   ‘miller’, a surname of German origin."],"variants":[{"name":"Millar","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Miller  . It is also found in Ireland (especially Antrim)."]},{"name":"Mueller","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Kurt, Otto, Hans, Erwin, Fritz, Gerhard, Klaus, Heinz, Helmut, Wolfgang, Manfred, Horst.","German (mainly <b>Müller</b>) and Jewish (Ashkenazic; also <b>Müller</b>); Dutch: occupational name for a miller, Middle High German <i>müller</i>, German <i>Müller</i>. In Germany, <i>Müller</i>, <i>Mueller</i> is the most frequent of all surnames; in the US it is often changed to   Miller   or appears as   Muller  . See also   Mulder  ."]},{"name":"Milner","meanings":["English (northern, especially Yorkshire): variant of   Miller  , retaining the <i>-n-</i> of the Middle English word <i>milnere</i> ‘miller’.","German: variant of <b>Müller</b> (see   Mueller  )."]},{"name":"Millward","meanings":["English (mainly West Midlands): occupational name from Middle English <i>milne-ward</i>, <i>mille-ward</i> ‘keeper of a mill, miller’ (Old English <i>mylen-weard</i>). In southern England and the West Midlands this was a standard medieval term for a miller. Compare   Miller  ."]},{"name":"McMiller","meanings":["Scottish: patronymic from the occupational byname   Miller  ."]}]},{"name":"Anne","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of   Ann   or   Anne ."],"variants":[{"name":"Anni","meanings":["Pet form of   Ann   or   Anne ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Anne Miller was born in 1531, in England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with Nicholas Posyer. She died in 1575, in Brasted, Kent, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 44."},"et":{"1531–1575":"1531–1575","1530–1575":"1530–1575","1542–Female":"1542–Surnud","1531":"1531","1542":"1542","1575":"1575","1530":"1530","Brasted, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Brasted, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1531–1575":"1531–1575","1530–1575":"1530–1575","1542–Female":"1542–Kuollut","1531":"1531","1542":"1542","1575":"1575","1530":"1530","Brasted, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Brasted, Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1531–1575":"1531–1575","1530–1575":"1530–1575","1542–Female":"1542–Décédée","1531":"1531","1542":"1542","1575":"1575","1530":"1530","Brasted, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Brasted, Kent, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England, United Kingdom":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Anne Miller est née en 1531, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec Nicholas Posyer. Elle est décédée en 1575, à Brasted, Kent, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, à l’âge de 44 ans."},"de":{"1531–1575":"1531–1575","1530–1575":"1530–1575","1542–Female":"1542–Verstorben","1531":"1531","1542":"1542","1575":"1575","1530":"1530","Brasted, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Brasted, Kent, England, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom